cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with image distortions and their effect on DNNs for computer vision tasks.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a new approach for training DNNs to correct for image distortions.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with improving the performance of DNNs for computer vision tasks.
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with deep neural networks and their performance.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely sub-category as the paper deals specifically with image distortions and their effect on DNNs for computer vision tasks, rather than multimedia in general.
